  <h3 id="user_pages">User Pages</h3>

  <p>Roughdraft is built with the GitHub API, so we can do some really cool stuff, like give every GitHub user their own Roughdraft namespace!</p>

  <p>Visit <code><b>username</b>.roughdraft.io</code> to see a list of all the public, Markdown-formatted Gists belonging to <code><b>username</b></code>.</p>

  <h3 id="formatting">Formatting</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>Your Gist&#8217;s <code>description</code> field will be used as the headline for your post.</li>
    <li>Roughdraft can render <a href="https://help.github.com/articles/github-flavored-markdown" target="new">GitHub-flavored Markdown</a>, <a href="http://redcloth.org/hobix.com/textile/">Textile</a>, <a href="http://haml.info/">Haml</a>, and plain text.</li>
    <li>Use images and <a href="http://www.emoji-cheat-sheet.com/" target="new">emoji</a>! <img class="emoji" title=":metal:" alt=":metal:" src="/images/emoji/metal.png" height="20" width="20" align="absmiddle"></li>
    <li>You can even <a href="http://jedfoster.roughdraft.io/5311961">embed other files from the same Gist</a> like this: <code>&lt;gist&gt;other_code.rb&lt;/gist&gt;</code>.</li>
  </ul>

